      "title": "Hamish Falconer MP",
      "description": "Hamish Falconer was appointed Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State at the Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office on 18 July 2024. He was elected as the MP for Lincoln in July 2024. Follow Hamish on X: @HFalconerMP .",
      "text": "Biography\n\nHamish Falconer was appointed Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State at the Foreign, Commonwealth and Development Office on 18 July 2024. He was elected as the MP for Lincoln in July 2024.\n\nFollow Hamish on X: @HFalconerMP.\n\nParliamentary Under-Secretary of State (Middle East, North Africa, Afghanistan and Pakistan)\n\nMiddle East and North Africa\n\nAfghanistan and Pakistan\n\nconsular and crisis\n\nMore about this role\n\nForeign, Commonwealth & Development Office\n\nAnnouncements\n\nSubscriptions\n\nGet emails\n\nFCDO summons Iranian Chargé d'Affaires over attack on Iran international journalist\n\n07 July 2026\n\nPress release\n\nUK deepens joint migration efforts and marks Pakistan’s role in brokering US-Iran peace deal on two-day Ministerial visit\n\n16 June 2026\n\nStatement: Summoning the Israeli Chargé d’Affaires\n\n21 May 2026\n\nSummoning of the Iranian Ambassador to the United Kingdom\n\n28 April 2026\n\nNew UK Aid for displaced people in Lebanon as Minister visits Beirut\n\n16 April 2026\n\nTwo years on, UK reiterates call for accountability for the World Central Kitchen strike in Gaza\n\n01 April 2026\n\nNews story\n\nMinister for the Middle East speech at the Driving International Trade Conference\n\n26 March 2026\n\nSpeech\n\nSummoning of the Iranian Ambassador to the United Kingdom: FCDO statement\n\n23 March 2026\n\nMajor community iftar held by ministers at Lancaster House\n\n10 March 2026\n\n04 March 2026\n\nView all announcements",
